&lt;h3&gt;Shabbat Sh&#039;kalim&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shabbat Sh&#039;kalim is the first of a series of five special Shabbatot before Passover. It is on the Shabbat before Rosh Chodesh Adar (Adar II, during leap years). In this week&#039;s additional Torah reading (Exodus 30:11-16), we read that every adult Jew contributed a half-shekel to the upkeep of the Tent of Meeting. The special Haftarah from II Kings commemorates the half-shekel each person contributed each year to the upkeep of the Temple. We commemorate this practice on Shabbat Sh&#039;kalim, because the financial year for the Temple began in Nisan, so the half-shekel was generally collected a month earlier, in Adar. On Purim, synagogues often gather contributions to the poor; these contributions are called &quot;machatzit ha&#039;shekel&quot; in memory of the half-shekel given in Temple times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading Scroll #2&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exodus 30:11-16 (P 632, RP 584, WTC 497)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Aliyah&lt;/p&gt;
